  "executive_summary": {
    "recommended_reading": "This is the first geometry-dependent laboratory signal model in the repository with an exact closed-form slab interaction law. It keeps the benchmark amplitude fixed at the reference gap but replaces the pure 1/a^4 extrapolation with a screened-field interaction shape.",
    "reference_statement": "At 0.2 um and alpha = 0.001, the planar slab model predicts 13.0014 uPa and 13.0014 pN for a 1 mm^2 active area.",
    "normalization_statement": "Matching the reference gap requires an effective slab source strength of 1.90039e+08, which corresponds to a conversion factor of 1.90039e-32 relative to the repository's laboratory decoherence-rate-density scale 1e+40. That is 1.13945e-30 times the naive causal screening scale 1/(c l_s). If read as a simple persistence-time bridge kappa = tau/l_s^2, the implied timescale is 7.60156e-46 s = 0.0140998 t_P.",
    "force_context_statement": "The reference differential force 13.0014 pN is 43.3379 times the 0.3 pN static-force absolute error quoted in the Decca 2003 Casimir measurement."
